d":"Cornwall, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir William Bodrugan was born about 1398, in Cornwall, England, his father, William Bodrugan, was 28 and his mother, Johanna Bodrugan, was 25. He married Phillipa Arundell about 1425, in Cornwall, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died on 24 December 1441, at the age of 44."},"et":{"about 1398–24 December 1441":"umbes 1398–24. detsember 1441","1396–1426":"1396–1426","1398–1441":"1398–1441","1404–1443":"1404–1443","1403–1445":"1403–1445","1426–1486":"1426–1486","1372–1416":"1372–1416","1375–Female":"1375–Surnud","1396":"1396","1372":"1372","1404":"1404","1426":"1426","from 7 November 1427 to 4 November 1428":"7. november 1427 kuni 4. november 1428","1403":"1403","1445":"1445","1443":"1443","1486":"1486","1398":"1398","about 1403":"umbes 1403","about 1425":"umbes 1425","June 1426":"juuni 1426","1375":"1375","1441":"1441","24 December 1441":"24. detsember 1441","about 1398":"umbes 1398","about 1397":"umbes 1397","1416":"1416","England":"England","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1398–24 December 1441":"noin 1398–24. joulukuuta 1441","1396–1426":"1396–1426","1398–1441"